items.title: Market snaps 3-week gaining streak amid Indo-Pak war tensions
items.description: The Indian rupee ended lower against the US dollar as domestic currency slipped 81 to end at 85.37 per dollar on May 9 against the May 2 closing of 84.56.

items.title: Wall Street closes near flat with focus on US-China talks
items.description: The Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 119.07 points, or 0.29%, to 41,249.38, the S&P 500 lost 4.03 points, or 0.07%, to 5,659.91 and the Nasdaq Composite gained 0.78 points, or flat, to 17,928.92.

items.title: Border tensions snap market's three-week gaining streak despite net FII buying for the week
items.description: The benchmark indices ended a three-week gaining streak with a one percent fall, with nearly 40 Nifty 50 names ending in the red on a weekly basis.
